snippet: The right-wing United Kingdom Independence Party failed to capitalize on a strong showing in European elections, but it cut into the Conservatives’ margin of victory.
abstract: Populist right-wing United Kingdom Independence Party fails to win its first seat in the British Parliament, finishing second to Conservative candidate in a special election.
lead_paragraph: The right-wing United Kingdom Independence Party failed to capitalize on a strong showing in European elections, but it cut into the Conservatives’ margin of victory.

headline.main: Populist Party Fails to Capture Seat in British Parliament
headline.print_headline: Britain: Populist Party Fails to Win Seat
